item.title: Free website developer
item.dc:creator: @Ruby_Forums_Coder Ruby
item.description:
@Ruby_Forums_Coder wrote:

[quote=“Mopman, post:4, topic:555476”][quote author=Ruby link=topic=674682.msg4509029#msg4509029 date=1464334717]
I can get a .com domain for £1
[/quote]

Then there’s a catch, because that’s far lower than cost price[/quote]

It’s not available all the time, if you sign up to the emailing lists of several large providers they often do “flash” sales in the last 2/3 days of the month (obviously to hit sale targets). Often it’s a bundle so register X and get it for X or take out a domain for a year and pay for a years hosting but you can 100% get them without too much trouble.

A lot of companies see it as an “in” for market share, get you in with a bit of a higher cost of acquisition but once you’re on board they’ll cross-sell the other parts that makes the profit in the long run.

Read full topic
